PSS.formatPatterns.markdownDescription:
## Pattern-Based Text Formatter

This feature formats text by aligning specific patterns within the content. It identifies instances of the given pattern and adjusts the surrounding text so that the patterns are neatly aligned across consecutive lines.
### Example

Given the following text (with pattern `=`):

```
    int a = 10;
    int test = 69;
    int unique = 42*10;
```

After formatting, it produces:

```
    int a      = 10;
    int test   = 69;
    int unique = 42*10;
```
